defs.docs: Rust wrapper around freetype 2 library

defs.name: None
defs.docs: This value is reserved.

defs.name: Mono
defs.docs:
A monochrome bitmap, using 1 bit per pixel. Note that pixels are
 stored in most-significant order (MSB), which means that the left-most
 pixel in a byte has value 128.

defs.name: Gray
defs.docs:
An 8-bit bitmap, generally used to represent anti-aliased glyph images.
 Each pixel is stored in one byte. Note that the number of `gray`
 levels is stored in the `num_grays` field of the FT_Bitmap structure
 (it generally is 256).

defs.name: Gray2
defs.docs:
A 2-bit per pixel bitmap, used to represent embedded anti-aliased
 bitmaps in font files according to the OpenType specification. We
 haven't found a single font using this format, however.

defs.name: Gray4
defs.docs:
A 4-bit per pixel bitmap, representing embedded anti-aliased bitmaps in
 font files according to the OpenType specification. We haven't found a
 single font using this format, however.

defs.name: Lcd
defs.docs:
An 8-bit bitmap, representing RGB or BGR decimated glyph images used
 for display on LCD displays; the bitmap is three times wider than the
 original glyph image. See also FT_RENDER_MODE_LCD.

defs.name: LcdV
defs.docs:
An 8-bit bitmap, representing RGB or BGR decimated glyph images used for
 display on rotated LCD displays; the bitmap is three times taller than
 the original glyph image. See also FT_RENDER_MODE_LCD_V.

defs.name: Bgra
defs.docs:
An image with four 8-bit channels per pixel, representing a color image
 (such as emoticons) with alpha channel. For each pixel, the format is
 BGRA, which means, the blue channel comes first in memory. The color
 channels are pre-multiplied and in the sRGB colorspace. For example,
 full red at half-translucent opacity will be represented as
 `00,00,80,80`, not `00,00,FF,80`. See also FT_LOAD_COLOR.

defs.name: PixelMode
defs.value: PixelMode::{None, Mono, Gray, Gray2, Gray4, Lcd, LcdV, Bgra}
defs.docs:
An enumeration type used to describe the format of pixels in a given bitmap. Note that
 additional formats may be added in the future.

defs.name: buffer
defs.docs:
A typeless pointer to the bitmap buffer. This value should be aligned
 on 32-bit boundaries in most cases.

defs.name: width
defs.docs: The number of pixels in bitmap row.

defs.name: rows
defs.docs: The number of bitmap rows.

defs.name: pixel_mode
defs.docs:
The pixel mode, i.e., how pixel bits are stored. See `PixelMode` for
 possible values.

defs.name: pitch
defs.docs:
The pitch's absolute value is the number of bytes taken by one bitmap row, including
 padding. However, the pitch is positive when the bitmap has a ‘down’ flow, and negative
 when it has an ‘up’ flow. In all cases, the pitch is an offset to add to a bitmap pointer
 in order to go down one row.

defs.name: get_cbox
defs.docs:
Return a glyph's ‘control box’. The control box encloses all the outline's points,
 including Bézier control points. Though it coincides with the exact bounding box for most
 glyphs, it can be slightly larger in some situations (like when rotating an outline that
 contains Bézier outside arcs).

defs.name: format
defs.docs:
An enumeration type used to describe the format of a given glyph image. Note that this
 version of FreeType only supports two image formats, even though future font drivers will
 be able to register their own format.

defs.name: render_glyph
defs.docs:
Convert a given glyph image to a bitmap. It does so by inspecting the glyph image format,
 finding the relevant renderer, and invoking it.

defs.name: get_subglyph_info
defs.docs:
Retrieve a description of a given subglyph. Only use it if the glyph's format is
 FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_COMPOSITE; an error is returned otherwise.

defs.name: get_glyph
defs.docs: Returns a glyph object, that is similar to a `GlyphSlot` but managed outside of the library

defs.name: outline
defs.docs:
In freetype, the `Outline` object is a scalable glyph. This method unpacks a glyph into
 this object, or returns `None` if the glyph has no `outline`

defs.name: bitmap
defs.docs:
This field is used as a bitmap descriptor when the slot format is FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_BITMAP.
 Note that the address and content of the bitmap buffer can change between calls of
 FT_Load_Glyph and a few other functions.

defs.name: bitmap_left
defs.docs:
The bitmap's left bearing expressed in integer pixels. Only valid if the format is
 FT_GLYPH_FORMAT_BITMAP, this is, if the glyph slot contains a bitmap.

defs.name: bitmap_top
defs.docs:
The bitmap's top bearing expressed in integer pixels. Remember that this is the distance
 from the baseline to the top-most glyph scanline, upwards y coordinates being positive.

defs.name: advance
defs.docs:
This shorthand is, depending on FT_LOAD_IGNORE_TRANSFORM, the transformed (hinted) advance
 width for the glyph, in 26.6 fractional pixel format. As specified with
 FT_LOAD_VERTICAL_LAYOUT, it uses either the ‘horiAdvance’ or the ‘vertAdvance’ value of
 ‘metrics’ field.

defs.name: linear_hori_advance
defs.docs:
The advance width of the unhinted glyph. Its value is expressed in 16.16 fractional pixels,
 unless FT_LOAD_LINEAR_DESIGN is set when loading the glyph. This field can be important to
 perform correct WYSIWYG layout. Only relevant for outline glyphs.

defs.name: linear_vert_advance
defs.docs:
The advance height of the unhinted glyph. Its value is expressed in 16.16 fractional
 pixels, unless FT_LOAD_LINEAR_DESIGN is set when loading the glyph. This field can be
 important to perform correct WYSIWYG layout. Only relevant for outline glyphs.

defs.name: metrics
defs.docs:
The metrics of the last loaded glyph in the slot. The returned values depend on the last
 load flags (see the FT_Load_Glyph API function) and can be expressed either in 26.6
 fractional pixels or font units.

This function is used to create a new FreeType library instance and add the default
 modules. It returns a struct encapsulating the freetype library. The library is correctly
 discarded when the struct is dropped.
